     8	// Beat-context store — the Direct-LLM source of truth for what the coach sees on
     9	// each onboarding beat. Two layers, both sent fresh every request (the LLM never
    10	// assumes it remembers anything):
    11	//
    12	//   GLOBAL_ONBOARDING_CONTEXT  — who the coach is, the Path 1/2/3 behavior, the
    13	//                                cross-beat rules. Sits above every beat.
    14	//   BEAT_CONTEXTS[screenId]    — the one thing to collect on this beat, the tools
    15	//                                allowed here, and the verbatim opener line.
    16	//
    17	// A beat context is the COACH layer only (no screen_id/route/NEXT/system-action/
    18	// Vapi machinery). Tools are gated structurally via `allowedTools`; the opener is
    19	// a verbatim string the coach renders word-for-word (it is the renderer, not the
    20	// author). Keyed by canonical screen_id (== beatForStep().screenId).
    21	//
    22	// Locked decisions (2026-06-24 call):
